WEBVTT

00:00:30.246 --> 00:00:30.387
Well,

00:00:30.426 --> 00:00:33.029
welcome to Family Hour of the Yahowah Blog.

00:00:33.409 --> 00:00:36.612
We're a little different this evening,

00:00:37.313 --> 00:00:39.395
just as a matter of happenstance,

00:00:39.454 --> 00:00:41.777
but it's like turning back the clock,

00:00:42.176 --> 00:00:43.378
twenty years.

00:00:43.639 --> 00:00:46.320
Dr. Jeff, you're here with me.

00:00:46.881 --> 00:00:49.423
We have you at home and we can

00:00:49.463 --> 00:00:50.024
converse.

00:00:50.445 --> 00:00:51.845
We don't have our good buddy,

00:00:52.405 --> 00:00:53.366
Captain Kirk,

00:00:53.387 --> 00:00:55.889
who was the second to become part of

00:00:55.929 --> 00:00:56.509
our family.

00:00:56.810 --> 00:01:00.273
Uh, he's, uh, made every effort to, uh,

00:01:00.313 --> 00:01:00.954
to join us,

00:01:01.393 --> 00:01:03.756
but we are going back and forth with

00:01:03.776 --> 00:01:05.757
him where either we can hear him or

00:01:05.817 --> 00:01:06.778
he can hear us,

00:01:07.138 --> 00:01:10.561
but we have not yet had a anything

00:01:10.602 --> 00:01:11.302
reciprocal,

00:01:11.763 --> 00:01:13.204
which is what you kind of need to

00:01:13.385 --> 00:01:15.447
make this work where he can hear us

00:01:15.486 --> 00:01:16.266
and we can hear him.

00:01:16.587 --> 00:01:18.969
He may get logged on and we may

00:01:19.010 --> 00:01:20.790
be able to make this work going forward.

00:01:20.831 --> 00:01:21.391
We hope so.

00:01:22.031 --> 00:01:22.733
And, uh,

00:01:22.893 --> 00:01:25.814
We know that JB is out on a

00:01:25.935 --> 00:01:27.936
family thing.

00:01:27.977 --> 00:01:30.998
He's got the time off and they're off,

00:01:31.159 --> 00:01:31.760
I believe,

00:01:31.920 --> 00:01:35.662
at the zoo enjoying one another's company,

00:01:35.683 --> 00:01:38.204
which is a lovely thing to do there

00:01:38.364 --> 00:01:39.805
and Dallas and

00:01:40.525 --> 00:01:40.906
Kevin,

00:01:40.986 --> 00:01:42.487
who is normally the one that gets

00:01:42.528 --> 00:01:45.150
everybody connected on this program,

00:01:45.790 --> 00:01:50.093
is out because his father-in-law has

00:01:50.153 --> 00:01:52.855
passed away and therefore he's doing the

00:01:53.555 --> 00:01:55.677
appropriate thing and supporting his

00:01:55.778 --> 00:01:58.980
mother and his wife in this time of

00:01:59.019 --> 00:01:59.540
their grief.

00:02:00.382 --> 00:02:04.566
And so we will not have Kevin.

00:02:05.147 --> 00:02:07.531
We may get a Kirk if he can

00:02:07.570 --> 00:02:08.912
both listen and talk.

00:02:08.991 --> 00:02:11.034
He has tried to come back into the

00:02:11.074 --> 00:02:11.534
studio.

00:02:11.555 --> 00:02:13.877
We'll just see if there's any way that

00:02:13.937 --> 00:02:14.399
that works.

00:02:14.419 --> 00:02:14.998
There's Kirk.

00:02:15.620 --> 00:02:15.919
Hello.

00:02:16.882 --> 00:02:18.103
There it is.

00:02:18.143 --> 00:02:20.105
Yes, we can hear we can hear Kirk.

00:02:20.205 --> 00:02:21.747
But can you hear us?

00:02:21.828 --> 00:02:22.187
Yes.

00:02:22.968 --> 00:02:23.770
Oh, my goodness.

00:02:24.110 --> 00:02:25.012
So here we are.

00:02:25.693 --> 00:02:27.455
What we have here then is the old

00:02:27.495 --> 00:02:27.974
timers.

00:02:28.395 --> 00:02:31.439
We are the three that all go back

00:02:31.539 --> 00:02:33.102
almost twenty years together.

00:02:34.180 --> 00:02:36.721
So we'll have a family hour of the

00:02:37.300 --> 00:02:37.920
old guys.

00:02:38.622 --> 00:02:41.082
And that's a positive thing to do.

00:02:41.182 --> 00:02:42.723
One of the things that I wanted to

00:02:42.802 --> 00:02:45.204
return to, guys,

00:02:45.243 --> 00:02:46.524
since we're here together,

00:02:46.645 --> 00:02:49.586
is how I left the last episode here.

00:02:49.626 --> 00:02:51.645
We were talking about the conditions in

00:02:51.705 --> 00:02:56.448
the Gan Eden and how we all over

00:02:56.508 --> 00:02:59.449
time are given this opportunity to learn.

00:02:59.588 --> 00:03:02.150
The number one thing that

00:03:02.907 --> 00:03:04.788
I came to understand as we were going

00:03:04.828 --> 00:03:08.368
through the narrative of Eden this time

00:03:09.028 --> 00:03:12.411
was that God was really quite disappointed

00:03:12.591 --> 00:03:18.573
in Adam and that he showed no interest

00:03:18.633 --> 00:03:19.592
in listening to him.

00:03:21.334 --> 00:03:24.474
He showed no interest in working with him.

00:03:25.795 --> 00:03:28.997
And he certainly wasn't responsive or

00:03:29.657 --> 00:03:31.578
engaged in a way that

00:03:32.501 --> 00:03:33.542
God could rely on him.

00:03:34.603 --> 00:03:37.544
And so the idea of having Adam in

00:03:37.564 --> 00:03:41.007
a relationship with Yahowah outside of the

00:03:41.067 --> 00:03:43.049
constraints of that garden just wasn't

00:03:43.068 --> 00:03:43.628
going to work.

00:03:44.729 --> 00:03:46.951
And God's ultimate idea is not to have

00:03:47.012 --> 00:03:51.835
us locked in a garden or even locked

00:03:51.895 --> 00:03:52.695
on this planet,

00:03:53.276 --> 00:03:55.698
but to expose us to the entire universe

00:03:55.717 --> 00:03:58.060
that he's created of two worlds.

00:03:58.723 --> 00:04:00.003
trillion galaxies,

00:04:00.063 --> 00:04:02.724
each with hundreds of billions of stars.

00:04:02.784 --> 00:04:04.686
It's so much more out there that he

00:04:04.725 --> 00:04:05.447
wants to share.

00:04:06.127 --> 00:04:08.808
It's just that Adam wasn't up to snuff

00:04:08.908 --> 00:04:10.469
and he wasn't going to get there.

00:04:11.629 --> 00:04:14.192
And so what we find is that God

00:04:14.231 --> 00:04:16.892
trying to cultivate a very different kind

00:04:17.213 --> 00:04:20.394
of interaction than what he experienced

00:04:21.115 --> 00:04:21.975
with Adam in the garden.

00:04:23.132 --> 00:04:25.533
And he wants someone who is willing to

00:04:25.572 --> 00:04:26.132
learn from him.

00:04:26.192 --> 00:04:27.113
Otherwise,

00:04:27.134 --> 00:04:29.454
what's the point of having a relationship

00:04:29.555 --> 00:04:31.995
and being as smart as God is and

00:04:32.036 --> 00:04:37.557
having all this to share if those he's

00:04:37.598 --> 00:04:39.759
trying to do this with have no interest

00:04:39.819 --> 00:04:41.639
in learning from him and engaging with

00:04:41.699 --> 00:04:41.819
him?

00:04:42.579 --> 00:04:45.161
And what that took me to is this

00:04:45.701 --> 00:04:48.903
whole process of how we have developed in

00:04:48.942 --> 00:04:51.363
our understanding over the years.

00:04:52.524 --> 00:04:56.528
Because nobody ever develops any character

00:04:57.910 --> 00:04:59.610
until they have stumbled,

00:05:00.072 --> 00:05:01.632
until life gets to be tough,

00:05:02.353 --> 00:05:04.355
until something gets in the way that makes

00:05:04.394 --> 00:05:04.956
it hard.

00:05:05.475 --> 00:05:06.997
That's how we develop character.

00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:08.918
Not that either of you two guys have

00:05:08.939 --> 00:05:11.461
ever had a difficult time, right?

00:05:13.663 --> 00:05:14.363
I play golf.

00:05:15.345 --> 00:05:17.947
You play golf.

00:05:17.987 --> 00:05:19.048
Your hobby is golf.

00:05:20.168 --> 00:05:21.028
You know all about it.

00:05:23.589 --> 00:05:24.391
I played the fifth.

00:05:25.011 --> 00:05:25.831
You played the fifth.

00:05:25.851 --> 00:05:28.274
Yeah, I know your history.

00:05:28.613 --> 00:05:29.694
You've had a few challenges.

00:05:30.055 --> 00:05:31.716
And when you overcome a challenge,

00:05:31.776 --> 00:05:33.778
it gives you great confidence, doesn't it?

00:05:33.877 --> 00:05:34.158
Yes.

00:05:35.514 --> 00:05:35.915
Absolutely.

00:05:35.995 --> 00:05:36.475
Absolutely.

00:05:36.514 --> 00:05:37.016
Absolutely.

00:05:37.036 --> 00:05:38.475
Because you know that life's going to

00:05:38.516 --> 00:05:39.076
bring another one.

00:05:39.096 --> 00:05:39.656
And when it does,

00:05:39.716 --> 00:05:43.677
you're proven that you can be counted on.

00:05:44.516 --> 00:05:45.298
You learn from it.

00:05:45.577 --> 00:05:47.158
And, you know, Kirk,

00:05:47.218 --> 00:05:49.038
I remember back in the day before you

00:05:49.079 --> 00:05:51.098
met the lovely Sylvia,

00:05:51.119 --> 00:05:53.800
that life wasn't quite as enjoyable as it

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:55.279
is now.

00:05:55.339 --> 00:05:55.899
And of course,

00:05:56.459 --> 00:05:58.961
right now you're dealing with a health

00:05:59.040 --> 00:06:01.442
issue that is zapping your strength,

00:06:01.482 --> 00:06:02.362
making it really tough.

00:06:02.841 --> 00:06:04.262
But look with your big smile.

00:06:04.322 --> 00:06:08.764
So you're able to deal with a rough

00:06:08.805 --> 00:06:09.146
blow.

00:06:10.026 --> 00:06:12.666
And it's the way life's supposed to be.

00:06:13.827 --> 00:06:15.028
One of the problems, I think,

00:06:15.088 --> 00:06:18.269
with Adam is that because he was in

00:06:18.329 --> 00:06:20.331
a protected and sheltered garden,

00:06:21.572 --> 00:06:22.572
there were no challenges.

00:06:23.593 --> 00:06:24.334
Plenty of food.

00:06:25.014 --> 00:06:26.035
Temperature was perfect.

00:06:27.334 --> 00:06:28.375
Company was great.

00:06:29.096 --> 00:06:30.797
There were no threats of any kind,

00:06:30.857 --> 00:06:31.958
no obstacles whatsoever.

00:06:33.055 --> 00:06:35.134
And under those circumstances,

00:06:35.175 --> 00:06:36.995
how do you grow?

00:06:37.036 --> 00:06:40.696
How do you prove to Yahowah that if

00:06:40.735 --> 00:06:43.036
there is a problem that you can get

00:06:43.156 --> 00:06:46.757
up and be trusted to grow from it?

00:06:49.077 --> 00:06:52.338
And so the whole idea is let's learn.

00:06:52.538 --> 00:06:53.478
Let's learn together.

00:06:53.499 --> 00:06:54.499
Let's grow together.

00:06:55.358 --> 00:06:57.560
Let's listen to what Yahowah has to say.

00:06:57.800 --> 00:06:59.819
And over time,

00:07:00.869 --> 00:07:02.990
develop a much more interesting

00:07:03.089 --> 00:07:07.112
relationship where we at least demonstrate

00:07:07.151 --> 00:07:08.911
that we're worth the time and effort

00:07:08.971 --> 00:07:11.452
because Adam was not worth the time and

00:07:11.512 --> 00:07:11.773
effort.

00:07:12.093 --> 00:07:13.954
It's kind of a sad situation,

00:07:13.994 --> 00:07:15.475
but nonetheless,

00:07:15.574 --> 00:07:17.115
not only wasn't he worth the time and

00:07:17.134 --> 00:07:17.336
effort,

00:07:17.355 --> 00:07:19.877
there was no chance that he was going

00:07:20.857 --> 00:07:23.658
to get there because for us to grow,

00:07:23.677 --> 00:07:25.798
we have to listen to Yahowah and he

00:07:25.819 --> 00:07:26.119
didn't.

00:07:27.800 --> 00:07:28.480
And for us to grow,

00:07:28.971 --> 00:07:31.031
develop a relationship that's meaningful,

00:07:31.132 --> 00:07:33.293
everybody has to engage and he didn't.

00:07:33.853 --> 00:07:35.214
And so one of the things we were

00:07:35.254 --> 00:07:41.057
talking about is that this relationship

00:07:41.177 --> 00:07:44.019
that we've all had and are developing with

00:07:44.060 --> 00:07:44.259
you,

00:07:44.699 --> 00:07:47.581
we have grown in what we have come

00:07:47.622 --> 00:07:49.103
to know and what we have come to

00:07:49.163 --> 00:07:49.742
understand.

00:07:50.624 --> 00:07:52.365
And that while you do that,

00:07:52.904 --> 00:07:56.586
there are going to be new evidence that

00:07:56.826 --> 00:07:57.867
you're going to consider

00:07:59.355 --> 00:08:01.115
You're observant of yes testimony.

00:08:01.456 --> 00:08:02.956
So you're going to have new evidence that

00:08:02.976 --> 00:08:03.877
you're going to consider.

00:08:04.216 --> 00:08:05.237
And as you do,

00:08:05.778 --> 00:08:09.759
you're going to have the opportunity to

00:08:09.798 --> 00:08:13.081
derive more complete understanding from

00:08:13.120 --> 00:08:15.401
that evidence.

00:08:15.521 --> 00:08:16.922
And I remember that.

00:08:17.391 --> 00:08:19.353
if you go back before the time that

00:08:19.394 --> 00:08:21.475
we recognized that Dowd was the,

00:08:22.336 --> 00:08:24.278
not only the Messiah and son of God,

00:08:24.598 --> 00:08:26.019
and therefore there could not have been a

00:08:26.079 --> 00:08:26.499
Jesus,

00:08:26.519 --> 00:08:28.521
because Dowd is the Messiah and son of

00:08:28.581 --> 00:08:28.880
God,

00:08:29.901 --> 00:08:32.283
but that Dowd volunteered to fulfill

00:08:32.403 --> 00:08:33.544
Pesach, Matzah, and Bikuwrym.

00:08:34.806 --> 00:08:36.528
And once you realize that,

00:08:36.687 --> 00:08:40.270
it changes your whole mindset and your

00:08:40.471 --> 00:08:42.072
appreciation of really everything that's

00:08:42.111 --> 00:08:42.832
in God's story.

00:08:42.852 --> 00:08:44.394
You know,

00:08:44.676 --> 00:08:46.417
Now you're able to see the greater and

00:08:46.716 --> 00:08:48.996
lesser luminaries for who they are in the

00:08:49.017 --> 00:08:50.097
fourth day of creation.

00:08:50.118 --> 00:08:52.097
You see the two trees of lives and

00:08:52.677 --> 00:08:54.778
of knowledge for who they are in the

00:08:54.818 --> 00:08:55.219
garden.

00:08:55.918 --> 00:08:59.460
And you recognize that this is how Yahowah

00:08:59.780 --> 00:09:04.142
made it possible for us to extend our

00:09:04.201 --> 00:09:09.263
lives and for us to resolve any issue

00:09:09.403 --> 00:09:12.825
in our lives by taking the guilt away,

00:09:13.424 --> 00:09:13.784
the guilt.

00:09:14.759 --> 00:09:17.419
is literally deposited in Sheowl,

00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:18.500
never to be seen again.

00:09:18.539 --> 00:09:21.201
So we look perfect in God's eyes,

00:09:21.240 --> 00:09:21.660
innocent.

00:09:22.360 --> 00:09:25.481
And I recall for the longest time not

00:09:25.601 --> 00:09:27.962
knowing that because, boy, that was,

00:09:28.082 --> 00:09:28.322
I think,

00:09:28.363 --> 00:09:30.222
the single greatest discovery we have come

00:09:30.263 --> 00:09:32.484
to in all of the twenty-four years we've

00:09:32.504 --> 00:09:33.104
been studying.

00:09:33.803 --> 00:09:35.764
And it was hidden in plain sight.

00:09:36.445 --> 00:09:38.905
The only reason we didn't perceive it

00:09:39.086 --> 00:09:43.706
sooner is that it's been covered over by

00:09:44.835 --> 00:09:45.735
religious muck.

00:09:45.875 --> 00:09:49.876
The most prominent religion in human

00:09:49.977 --> 00:09:53.119
history has literally stolen God's

00:09:53.198 --> 00:09:56.921
identity and created this myth of Jesus

00:09:57.000 --> 00:09:59.001
and piled all of their rubbish right on

00:09:59.042 --> 00:09:59.922
top of the truth.

00:10:00.342 --> 00:10:02.884
So it's very hard to get to the

00:10:02.964 --> 00:10:03.943
point where you say, wait a minute,

00:10:03.984 --> 00:10:05.304
there was no Jesus.

00:10:05.524 --> 00:10:07.546
He was nothing but a product of identity

00:10:07.586 --> 00:10:07.846
theft.

00:10:08.746 --> 00:10:10.628
The Messiah and Son of God who fulfilled

00:10:11.388 --> 00:10:13.448
Passover through crucifixion

00:10:14.494 --> 00:10:15.195
is Dowd David.

00:10:15.215 --> 00:10:15.955
He wrote about it.

00:10:16.676 --> 00:10:18.356
And that means it was Dowd who took

00:10:18.417 --> 00:10:19.719
our guilt into shield.

00:10:22.201 --> 00:10:24.241
Once you come to that point, you realize,

00:10:24.302 --> 00:10:24.543
you know,

00:10:24.582 --> 00:10:29.407
there is no functionality here to ascribe

00:10:29.506 --> 00:10:32.408
to the spirit of Yahowah,

00:10:32.428 --> 00:10:35.552
the Ruach of Yahowah, covering our guilt,

00:10:35.672 --> 00:10:37.874
which is the way that I tried to

00:10:37.933 --> 00:10:38.835
explain, well,

00:10:38.875 --> 00:10:40.296
how in the world does matzah work?

00:10:40.336 --> 00:10:40.836
How are we

00:10:41.953 --> 00:10:44.495
How do we appear right before God?

00:10:46.258 --> 00:10:47.759
Until you know that Dowd took our guilt

00:10:47.799 --> 00:10:50.942
into Sheowl, you need some mechanism.

00:10:51.003 --> 00:10:55.246
And my conclusion at the time was, well,

00:10:55.307 --> 00:10:58.750
then it's the spirit of Yahowah that covers

00:10:58.830 --> 00:11:01.312
us in light and where there is light,

00:11:01.331 --> 00:11:02.452
there is no darkness.

00:11:03.153 --> 00:11:06.096
But that really doesn't work.

00:11:07.400 --> 00:11:08.142
for lots of reasons.

00:11:08.241 --> 00:11:09.844
One is God never mentions the,

00:11:09.984 --> 00:11:11.566
and there is no place where we're told

00:11:11.625 --> 00:11:14.649
that the Spirit fulfilled matzah.

00:11:16.869 --> 00:11:18.350
So you're writing her into it.

00:11:18.450 --> 00:11:20.671
And I wrote her into the story because,

00:11:20.791 --> 00:11:22.191
well, at Matzah,

00:11:22.230 --> 00:11:25.373
we're encouraged to approach the Etsah,

00:11:25.432 --> 00:11:26.253
which is fire,

00:11:26.312 --> 00:11:27.933
but it's written in the feminine form.

00:11:27.974 --> 00:11:29.214
And I made too big a deal out

00:11:29.254 --> 00:11:30.375
of that and said, well,

00:11:30.394 --> 00:11:33.115
it might be a feminine manifestation of

00:11:33.775 --> 00:11:35.417
Yahowah's nature that we're supposed to be

00:11:35.456 --> 00:11:35.917
approaching,

00:11:36.397 --> 00:11:38.097
as opposed to recognizing that

00:11:38.842 --> 00:11:41.865
We approach the fire because that's the

00:11:41.905 --> 00:11:42.806
transformation.

00:11:42.885 --> 00:11:46.229
We get rid of our physical bodies and

00:11:46.369 --> 00:11:49.030
they are transformed into light energy so

00:11:49.052 --> 00:11:51.352
that our soul is enveloped in light

00:11:51.432 --> 00:11:51.833
energy.

00:11:53.034 --> 00:11:57.258
And that the spirit actually accompanied

00:11:57.317 --> 00:11:59.200
Dowd into Sheowl.

00:12:00.520 --> 00:12:01.841
Spirit didn't take our guilt there.

00:12:02.743 --> 00:12:04.224
All the purpose of the spirit was to

00:12:04.323 --> 00:12:07.066
protect Dowd's nephesh soul while he took

00:12:07.105 --> 00:12:07.626
our guilt there.

00:12:08.788 --> 00:12:10.190
And once you understand that,

00:12:10.451 --> 00:12:12.712
you don't need God to give you something

00:12:12.993 --> 00:12:17.798
to cover up your guilt because it's gone.

00:12:17.898 --> 00:12:24.024
And that led to the realization that there

00:12:24.085 --> 00:12:28.369
is no role for the set-apart spirit and

00:12:28.428 --> 00:12:29.831
the fulfillment of matzah,

00:12:29.951 --> 00:12:31.972
and it's all through Dowd.

00:12:32.591 --> 00:12:34.792
